⚙️ Technologies Used
HTML5 – semantic structure

CSS3 – responsive layout with media queries

JavaScript (Vanilla) – interactivity and animation triggers

Three.js – 3D model rendering in browser

Spline (Optional) – Web-based 3D viewer integration (fallback option)

📦 How to Run Locally
Clone the Repo

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-portfolio.git
cd your-portfolio
Install Live Server (or use any HTTP server)

bash
Copy
Edit
npm install -g live-server
live-server
Alternatively, just open index.html directly in a browser.

🧠 Key Components
Component	Description
#header	Hero section with name, role, and 3D background
.name	Custom-styled name with dynamic color on initial letter
#about	Skills and bio in two-column responsive layout
#projects	Grid-based project gallery with animated overlays
#contact	Contact form with icons and social media links
<canvas>	DOM node where Three.js renders the 3D scene
three-canvas	Styled via CSS for proper scaling across devices

🧪 Troubleshooting
3D model not visible?
✅ Confirm camera.position.z is set
✅ Ensure lighting (DirectionalLight, AmbientLight) is added
✅ Check the model path and file type (.glb/.gltf/.obj)

Canvas not resizing?
Use window.addEventListener('resize', ...) to auto-adjust renderer size.

📱 Responsive Design
Media queries optimize the layout for devices up to 768px. Mobile-specific tweaks include:

Hamburger navigation menu with toggle icon

Reduced font sizes and header image

3D section height capped (60vh) to prevent scroll bloat

📤 Deployment
You can host it on:

GitHub Pages

Vercel / Netlify

Firebase Hosting
(HTML-only site with no build process can be deployed in seconds.)

